## Q1
The database design prevents some data from being stored due to ______.
- ⭕ Deletion anomalies
- ✅ Insertion anomalies
- ⭕ Update anomalies
- ⭕ None of these

## Q2
A relation is in 2NF if:
- ⭕ All the values of non-key attributes are dependent fully on the candidate key.
- ⭕ Any non-key attribute that are dependent on only part of the candidate key should be moved to another relation where the partial key is the actual full key.
- ⭕ It must be already in the 1NF.
- ✅ All of the above.

## Q3
If one attribute is determinant of second, which in turn is determinant of third, (A->B and B->C) then the relation cannot be:
- ⭕ Well-structured
- ⭕ 1NF
- ⭕ 2NF
- ✅ 3NF

